    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">ok, the idea of this deck is to get out boromir + gandalf asap, with treebeard as help vs uruks. treebeard is also nice as healing tech when you dont have the right companion in hand. i feel that the FP is mostly self explanatory, as its nothing all that new, except its trust with only 4 guys, as opposed to 7 or 9 or something huge. im sure this has been done before, and any half decent player should know why i picked the cards i did (and any good player should wonder what the hell i was thinking when i picked them). the same pretty much goes for the shadow side. the idea is to cycle all your extra FP weapons and useless crap for shadow to get as many archers as you can out. i generally try to wait til after site 3 to start plinging at them. if you can get one guy dead with a few extra wounds by site six, you are doing just fine, and around site 8 they should get overwhelmed as most of their companions drop like flies and frodo is left to take the heat. now play it right. dont just drop cave troll with hammer when they have souped up gorn with armor... 2 wounds for 11 twilight is not efficent. dump the troll and get out a troop and some other guys to get the archery wounds. other than that, just play it by ear. sorry for the lack of detail, but its late, and i dont care much :)<br />
<br />
--Loaf </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
